# Batch Orchestration Protocol

This rule file defines how schema-level mass documentation is planned, executed, and resumed across agent sessions. It coordinates between `index-management.mdc` (tracking) and `context-handoff.mdc` (cross-batch knowledge).

**Execution model**: Plan + Execute run as a single uninterrupted flow within one session. The agent plans the batch, documents every object inline (no subagents), updates tracking in bulk at the end, and prints a summary. No user input required between start and finish.

> **⛔ ONE BATCH PER SESSION — HARD ENFORCEMENT**
>
> Each agent session processes **exactly one batch**. After completing a batch (bulk-update `_index.md`, write context handoff, print end-of-batch banner), the agent **MUST STOP**. Do NOT plan, queue, or begin the next batch. The operator starts a new session for each subsequent batch. In production, batch iteration is automated via a clause loop — the agent is never responsible for multi-batch sequencing. This constraint exists because context window limitations degrade documentation quality when multiple batches share a session. **Violating this rule is a hard failure.**

---

## Configuration Constants

```
DEFAULT_BATCH_SIZE       = 10      # Objects per wiki batch. Lowered from 25 to prevent context degradation on later objects.
STALENESS_THRESHOLD_DAYS = 30      # Skip objects documented within this many days (FR-008).
```

For V1, these are edited in this rule file directly. Command-argument overrides are deferred to a future iteration.

